import React, { useEffect, useState } from "react"; import Navbar from "../Components/Navbar.js"; import "./HospitalList.css"; // CSS file for styling import axios from "axios"; import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next'; function Hospital() { const { t } = useTranslation(); const [hospitals, setHospitals] = useState([]); useEffect(() => { axios .get("/api/hospitals/") .then((response) => { setHospitals(response.data); }) .catch((error) => { console.error("There was an error fetching the data!", error); }); }, []); return ( <>

{t('hospitalList.title')}

{t('hospitalList.description')}

{hospitals.map((hospital) => (

{hospital.name}

{t('hospitalList.address')}: {hospital.location}

{t('hospitalList.location')}

{t('hospitalList.services')}

{t('hospitalList.book')}

))}

{t('footer.title')}

{t('footer.description')}

{t('footer.services')}

{t('footer.conditions')} {t('footer.listings')} {t('footer.whatWeOffer')} {t('footer.howItWorks')} {t('footer.latestNews')}

{t('footer.usefulLinks')}

{t('footer.about')} {t('footer.services')} {t('footer.hospitals')} {t('footer.contact')}

{t('footer.followUs')}

{t('footer.facebook')} {t('footer.telegram')} {t('footer.whatsapp')} {t('footer.twitter')} {t('footer.instagram')}

{t('footer.contactUs')}

{t('footer.email')} {t('footer.phone')}
{/* Add content here if needed */}
); } export default Hospital;
